<br>
RULES:<br>
<br>
Thursday raids are going to be the day for those that would like a chance to raid something that you have been interested in running.  This is your chance to train as a raid leader for bigger hits.  I will try to attend all thursday raids and will serve as the Mentor Raid leader.  Depending on how the raid goes - you may see me step in and make groups or send you some (or a lot of)tells, or give some direction at certain points of the raid - don't take offence, its part of the learning - I didn't have anyone around to mentor me when I learned how to Raid lead.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> If you are not on the approved list - posted by Jahras, please clear thru him or Pensfan before posting any raid other than on Thursday.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
ONCE you have made the first bid on a specific Thursday.  You can not sign up as a new Raid Leader for a Thursday Raid until yours is done.<br>
<br>
DO not plan a Raid on a Thursday if someone has already called it.<br>
<br>
ONCE you have posted your Raid - make a Thread in this forum for your raid conduct signups and planning in that thread NOT HERE.<br>
<br>
INCLUDE the following information in your raid:<br>
- Raid Leader<br>
- Date<br>
- Location and Assembly area<br>
- Show time (what time players must arrive / be on channel)<br>
- raid channel name<br>
- Level range for raid.  PLEASE include a realistic range for a raid - I would recomend you not invite anyone 10 levels below the average level of monsters - but you are the raid leader it is YOUR Call.<br>
- prefered number of attendees - 2 - 3 groups<br>
- goal<br>
- additional comments / link to the actual raid thread etc<br>
<br>
EXAMPLE:<br>
RL: Serano<br>
Date: 13 June 02<br>
Loc: City of Mist - assemble at the Zone in area from EJ<br>
Show Time: NO later than 830PM EST<br>
Raid Channel : RastaJade<br>
Level Range: 40 to 60 (NEED ONE level 50 or higher Rogue with PL201 or better)<br>
Number of players : Zerg ( 18 or more)<br>
goal: Get a Jade Reaver for Meeras<br>
extra: Shammy epic drops are very common while doing this zone so - Shammys are very welcome - Raid is canceled at 9 PM if no over LP200 or with mod% Rogues show up.  Find Raid thread at xxxxx<br>
<br>
If guild officers would like to add to the posting rules of this thread - please post them here and I will cut and paste it to this main thread.<br>
